britons are now drinking on average only eight cups of tea a week they drank 23 cups in 1974 .
tea is still the most popular hot drink in the uk but people now spend more money on coffee .
the data comes from 150,000 families who took part in the survey between 1974 and 2000 , combined with information from 2000 to 2014 .
